710411f.title: Manhattan: 9th Avenue - 49th Street (West)
710411f.text:
Ninth Ave., south from West 49th Street, showing W.P.A. employees
removing street car tracks. Overhead is the Ninth Ave. Elevated Line.
May 8, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

713424f-a.title: Manhattan: 49th Street (West) - 9th Avenue
713424f-a.text:
404 West 49th Street, south side, just west of Ninth Avenue.
This is a three-story frame building with a stucco front.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 208.

713425f-a.title: Manhattan: 49th Street (West) - 9th Avenue
713425f-a.text:
409-411 West 49th Street, west of the N.W. corner of Ninth Ave.
Buildings concerned are 3-story frame houses, and are set back from Street
front.
September 22, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

713426f-a.title: Manhattan: 49th Street (West) - 9th Avenue
713426f-a.text:

Negative No. 206
